# Environment Variables for AI Calling Agents Module
# Domain: admin.tasknova.io

## ============================================
## REQUIRED - Supabase Configuration
## ============================================
# Go to: https://app.supabase.com → Your Project → Settings → API

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

## ============================================
## REQUIRED - IndusLabs API Configuration
## ============================================
# Go to: https://developer.induslabs.io → API Keys

INDUSLABS_API_KEY=

## ============================================
## REQUIRED - Webhook Configuration
## ============================================
# Callback URL where IndusLabs sends webhook events
# Production: https://admin.tasknova.io/api/webhooks/ai-agents/indus
# Development: http://localhost:3000/api/webhooks/ai-agents/indus

WEBHOOK_CALLBACK_URL=https://admin.tasknova.io/api/webhooks/ai-agents/indus

## ============================================
## OPTIONAL - Call Settings
## ============================================
# Minimum call duration in seconds to be considered valid
MIN_CALL_DURATION=10

# Evaluation score threshold (0-100)
# Calls below this score are flagged as needing attention
EVALUATION_THRESHOLD=50

## ============================================
## OPTIONAL - Feature Flags
## ============================================
# Enable/disable specific features
ENABLE_CALL_RECORDING=true
ENABLE_AUTO_EVALUATION=true
ENABLE_AUDIT_LOGGING=true

---

## ✅ Setup Checklist

### Step 1: Copy Environment File
```bash
cp .env.ai-agents.example .env.local
```

### Step 2: Fill in Supabase Credentials
1. Go to https://app.supabase.com
2. Select your project
3. Settings → API
4. Copy and paste into .env.local:
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

### Step 3: Get IndusLabs API Key
1. Go to https://developer.induslabs.io
2. Login to developer account
3. API Keys section
4. Copy API key to INDUSLABS_API_KEY in .env.local

### Step 4: Run Database Migration
```bash
supabase migration up
```

### Step 5: Start Development Server
```bash
npm run dev
```

### Step 6: Configure via UI (Optional)
- Navigate to: http://localhost:3000/admin/ai-calling-agents
- Go to "Settings" tab
- You can also configure settings through the UI instead of environment variables

### Step 7: Test Setup
- Go to http://localhost:3000/admin/ai-calling-agents
- All tabs should load without errors
- Check browser console for any errors

---

## 🔑 Required Keys Reference

| Variable | Source | How to Get |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL | Supabase | https://app.supabase.com → Settings → API → URL |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY | Supabase | https://app.supabase.com → Settings → API → anon key |
| SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY | Supabase | https://app.supabase.com → Settings → API → service_role |
| INDUSLABS_API_KEY | IndusLabs | https://developer.induslabs.io → API Keys |
| WEBHOOK_CALLBACK_URL | Your Domain | https://admin.tasknova.io/api/webhooks/ai-agents/indus |

---

## 🌐 Domain Configuration

**Your Domain**: admin.tasknova.io

**Webhook URL**: https://admin.tasknova.io/api/webhooks/ai-agents/indus

Make sure to:
- Point admin.tasknova.io to your server
- Have HTTPS certificate installed
- Ensure webhook URL is publicly accessible

---

## 📋 Configuration via Settings UI

After starting the dev server, you can also configure these settings through the Settings tab:
- IndusLabs API Key
- Webhook Callback URL
- Minimum Call Duration
- Evaluation Threshold

Settings saved through the UI are stored in the database and override environment variables.

# Check console for any errors
# Verify API calls are working in Network tab

# If you see "Unauthorized" errors:
# - Check Supabase credentials are correct
# - Verify user is authenticated
# - Check RLS policies in Supabase dashboard
```

---

## Production Deployment

Before deploying to production:

1. **Update environment variables** on your hosting platform
2. **Update callback URL** to production domain
3. **Enable HTTPS** (required for webhooks)
4. **Test webhook delivery** in IndusLabs dashboard
5. **Configure CORS** if needed
6. **Setup monitoring** for errors
7. **Test full call flow** end-to-end

---

## Support

If you encounter issues:

1. Check logs in browser console (F12)
2. Check server logs in terminal
3. Verify all environment variables are set
4. Check Supabase dashboard for errors
5. Review documentation: `/documentation/AI_CALLING_AGENTS_GUIDE.md`
